The 2017 Law of the Government of Wales gives the Assembly of Wales all the power to change its name.
In June, the committee published the results of a public consultation on the proposals, with broad support for the proposal to change the name of the assembly to that of the Welsh Parliament.
As for the title of the members of the assembly, although the committee chose "Members of the Welsh Parliament" or "WPM", the option of "MWP" is the one that received the most broad support in the public consultation.
