2006: A magnitude 6.8 earthquake struck southern Java, Indonesia's most populous island, and caused a tsunami that shattered the southern coast and killed nearly 700 people.
2009: An earthquake with a magnitude of 7.6 rocked a pop area of the city of Padang, the capital of West Sumatra province.
More than 1,100 people died.
2010: An earthquake with a magnitude of 7.5 shook one of the islands of Mentawai off the coast of Sumatra and caused a tsunami of up to 10 meters that destroyed dozens of villages and killed some 300 people.
2016: A mild earthquake struck the regency of Pidie Jaya in Aceh and caused destruction and panic, as the population recalled the devastation of the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
